FAQ

(Q) What is needed to compile gubbins?

(A) The libraries deal.II, PETSc, and SLEPc. That is, you need to
    successfully have installed deal.II with PETSc and SLEPc on your
    machine before gubbins will configure.

(Q) How do I compile gubbins?

(A) The safe way to compile gubbins is "out of source". (i) Make a
    build directory parallel to the gubbins root directory $ mkdir
    gubbins-build; (ii) run cmake $ cmake ../gubbins; and finally
    build the library with $ make. The shared library is built in
    gubbins/lib.